NAME - ::<namespace>:: ptp_over_mac_config

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork-NGPF

Performs ptp_over_mac configuration. Manages a device group of PTP clocks.

IxNetwork

Performs ptp_over_mac configuration

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

-mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

 

The operation this command will execute

Valid options are:

create

creates and configures a new object

add

adds a child object to the one specified by the -handle param

modify

modified attributes on the given object by the -handle param

delete

deletes the object given by the -handle param

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF [M]

DESCRIPTION

create - creates and configures a new object add - not supported in case of ::ixiangpf::ptp_over_mac_config. modify - modified attributes on the given object by the -handle param delete - deletes the object given by the -handle param

Valid options are:

create

Creates and configures a new object.

add

Not supported in case of ::ixiangpf::ptp_over_ip_config.

modify

Modified attributes on the given object by the -handle param.

delete

Deletes the object given by the -handle param.

DEFAULT

 None

vlan_id_step

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

If the -vlan_id_mode is increment, this will be the step value by which the VLAN tags are incremented. RANGE 0-4095 When vlan_id_step causes the vlan_id value to exceed it's maximum value the increment will be done modulo . Examples: vlan_id = 4094; vlan_id_step = 2 -> new vlan_id value = 0 vlan_id = 4095; vlan_id_step = 11 -> new vlan_id value = 10

DEFAULT

1

Valid in combination with parameter(s)
'vlan_id_mode' | value= 'increment' |
